{"lemma":"حَيّاتُ","slug":"حَيّاتُ","root":"ح.#.#","root_slug":"ح-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَيَّة","root":"حيي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9654","n9672"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"snake, serpent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"worm, wyrm"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of حَيّ (ḥayy)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ح و ي (ḥ w y), meaning \"to wrap around\", \"to wiggle or twist\", \"to writhe\", \"to coil\", \"to circle around a location\", \"to draw or gather together\"; related to the root ح ي و (ḥ y w), meaning \"a living space or enclosure\", \"a surrounding or vicinity\", \"a collection of tents circling around a campsite\". Cognate with Aramaic חויא (ḥiwyā), Classical Syriac ܚܘܝܐ (ḥewyā)."},"ipa":["/ħaj.ja/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9654","headword_ar":"حَيَّةٌ","root":"HwY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A serpent"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said by some to be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHaw~aY","text_ar":"تَحَوَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", because what is so termed gathers itself together, and winds, or coils, itself; (ISd, * K, * TA;) and to be originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawoyapN","text_ar":"حَوْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HY","text_ar":"حى"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and their opinion is strengthened by the forms and meaning of the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haw~aA='N","text_ar":"حَوَّا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAwK","text_ar":"حَاوٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) [and by the form and meaning of the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHowaApN","text_ar":"مَحْوَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hy~p","text_ar":"حيّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is so called because of the length of its life ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liTuwli HayaAtihaA","text_ar":"لِطُولِ حَيَاتِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (K. [See the next art.])"}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n9672","headword_ar":"حَيَّةٌ","root":"HY: or HY and Hyw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A serpent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain thing well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) [improperly explained in the Msb as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEFY","text_ar":"اَفْعًى"},{"kind":"text","text":":] applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being added to denote one of a kind, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baT~apN","text_ar":"بَطَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dajaAjapN","text_ar":"دَجَاجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [although"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N","text_ar":"حَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not used as a coll. gen. n.; and] although the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Hay~apK","text_ar":"عَلَى حَيَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu Hay~FA","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ حَيًّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"serpent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon a female"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"serpent"},{"kind":"text","text":"], is related as having been heard from the Arabs: (S:) but ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~uwtN","text_ar":"حَيُّوتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, K;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"being augmentative; for the word is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~uw","text_ar":"حَيُّو"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~uw~N","text_ar":"حَيُّوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Az, TA:) it is said that it does not die unless by an accident: and they say of a long-lived man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA huwa A_il~aA Hay~apN","text_ar":"مَا هُوَ اـِلَّا حَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is none other than a serpent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and in like manner they say of a woman; as though it were called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hy~p","text_ar":"حيّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of its long life: [for] some, including Sb, say that it is derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaApN","text_ar":"حَيَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as the rel. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayawiY~N","text_ar":"حَيَوِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawawiY~N","text_ar":"حَوَوِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and to him who objects that one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN Haw~aA='N","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ حَوَّا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning “ a man who collects serpents ”], it is replied that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~apN","text_ar":"حَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haw~aA='N","text_ar":"حَوَّا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are of different roots, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luw^oluw^N","text_ar":"لُوْلُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^~lN","text_ar":"لَاّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.: but it may be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHaw~aY","text_ar":"تَحَوَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", because of its winding, or coiling, itself; and some say that it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawoyapN","text_ar":"حَوْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; some, that it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayowapN","text_ar":"حَيْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [the dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huyay~apN","text_ar":"حُيَيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~aAtN","text_ar":"حَيَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayowaAtN","text_ar":"حَيْوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayawaAtN","text_ar":"حَيَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (So in some copies of the K [agreeably with the dial. of Hudheyl].) Hence the prov."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^aboSaru mino Hay~apK","text_ar":"هُوَ اَبْصَرُ مِنْ حَيَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is more sharp-sighted than a serpent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because of the sharpness of its sight: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZolamu","text_ar":"اَظْلَمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino Hay~apK","text_ar":"مِنْ حَيَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more wrongful in conduct than a serpent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because it comes to the burrow of the [lizard called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~","text_ar":"ضَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and eats its young one, and takes up its abode in its burrow. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqaAhu A@ll~`hu dama AlHay~aAti","text_ar":"سَقَاهُ ا@للّٰهُ دَمَ الحَيَّاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God give him to drink the blood of the serpents"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroy him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA talidu AlHay~apu A_il~aA Huyay~apF","text_ar":"لَا تَلِدُ الحَيَّةُ اـِلَّا حُيَيَّةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The serpent does not bring forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"save a little serpent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a prov. applied to the cunning and mischievous, or malignant. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Hay~apu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ حَيَّةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"الوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaladi","text_ar":"البَلَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamaATi","text_ar":"الحَمَاطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is cunning and mischievous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"malignant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and intelligent, in the utmost degree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar:) [or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"flAn Hy~p AlwAdY","text_ar":"فلان حيّة الوادى"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is strong in resisting, a defender of his possessions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~apu AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"حَيَّةُ الوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also an appellation applied to (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) because of his cunning, or craftiness. (TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo Hay~apu AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"هُمْ حَيَّةُ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are cunning, guileful, malignant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischievous, and strong, not neglecting to take blood-revenge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in a saying of Dhu-l-Isba' El-'Adwánee cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*iyrN","text_ar":"عَذِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Hay~apN *akarN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ حَيَّةٌ ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is courageous and strong."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osuhu raA^osu Hay~apK","text_ar":"رَاْسُهُ رَاْسُ حَيَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is clever,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ingenious; acute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp; intelligent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu fY kitaAbihi","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ فى كِتَابِهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~aAti waEaqaAriba","text_ar":"حَيَّاتِ وَعَقَارِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw in his letter slanders,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calumnies, addressed to the ruling power, in order to cause the object thereof to fall into embarrassment from which escape would be difficult."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHay~apu","text_ar":"الحَيَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a name of (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The constellation Draco;"},{"kind":"text","text":"commonly called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~in~iynu","text_ar":"التِّنِّينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"partly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroqadaAni","text_ar":"فَرْقَدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"B and y of Ursa Minor"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu naEo$K","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ نَعْشٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stars in the tail of Ursa Major"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) so called by way of comparison. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~apN","text_ar":"حَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain mark made with a hot iron upon the neck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the thigh, of a camel, twisting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"winding, like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~ap","text_ar":"حَيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"properly so called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ibn- Habeeb, TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N","text_ar":"حَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Az","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}